<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<job id="recruitment-morning-brief" xmlns="http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee" version="1.0">
    <!--
    Recruitment Morning Brief Job (ATS expansion Phase 23)

    Purpose:
    One morning Slack DM per interviewer on days they have scheduled
    interviews (Slack spec §5.8): candidate, position, round (or
    informal chat), time and place, the template's focus areas, the
    kit deep link and - when recruitment.slack.scorecard.enabled is
    on - a "Fill in scorecard" button per round. No interviews that
    day means no message.

    Every briefed (interviewer, interview) pair appends its own
    MORNING_BRIEF_SENT event carrying brief_date; the run only briefs
    pairs with no event for today, so re-runs and concurrent
    instances (ECS cutover) never double-DM. Only interviews in
    SCHEDULED state at run time brief - rescheduling is respected by
    construction. All side effects are gated by
    recruitment.pipeline.enabled AND
    recruitment.slack.morning-brief.enabled (off = no-op).

    Schedule:
    Daily at 06:00 UTC via BatchScheduler (07:00/08:00 Copenhagen -
    before the workday and before the 07:00 UTC SLA sweep), gated by
    dk.trustworks.recruitment.morning-brief.enabled (default true).

    Similar to:
    recruitment-sla-sweep.xml (the P17 clock-driven sweep)
    -->

    <listeners>
        <listener ref="jobMonitoringListener"/>
    </listeners>

    <step id="send-recruitment-morning-briefs">
        <listeners>
            <listener ref="stepProgressListener"/>
        </listeners>

        <batchlet ref="recruitmentMorningBriefBatchlet"/>
    </step>
</job>
